UI {{{1

zoom in                                 «C-+»
zoom out                                «C--»
reset zoom level to default             «C-0»

resize columns                          «C-S-r»
# resize packet list columns to fit contents; useful after changing zoom level

change layout                           «C-S-p»
                                        > Appearance
                                        > Layout

Capture {{{1

# Warning: These key bindings  might not work if you focus  an input field (e.g.
# the display filter  area), or some others  elements of the UI.  In  case of an
# issue, press Tab to focus a different element.

start/stop capture                      «C-e»
# To limit the capture to a specific interface, select it in the welcome screen.
# "any" means all interfaces simultaneously.

restart capture                         «C-r»

close capture file                      «C-w»

Filter {{{1

# to type in the capture filter to filter out packets based on given:
port                                    tcp.port == ‹port›
IPv4                                    ip.addr == ‹IPv4›
IPv6                                    ipv6.addr == ‹IPv6›

filter out given protocol               not ‹protocol›
filter out packets sent to given IP     ip.dst != ‹IP›

connect filters with logical AND        ‹filter1› and ‹filter2›

# to press to follow:
HTTP stream                             «C-M-S-h»
TCP stream                              «C-M-S-t»
TLS stream                              «C-M-S-s»
UDP stream                              «C-M-S-u»

filter out noise                        not arp and not bt-dht and not dns and not icmp and not igmp and not mdns and not nbns and not uaudp and ip.dst != 91.121.58.181 and ip.dst != 87.98.149.171
# I think the IP addresses are our current DNS servers.
# Also, `uaudp` is for "Universal  Alcatel/UDP Encapsulation Protocol"; it seems
# to be used by `transmission-daemon(1)`.

Packet {{{1

go to given packet                      «C-g»
# then type packet number in new input field

expand packet details                   «C-Right»
# only works if you focus the packet details pane

Misc {{{1

list of keyboard shortcuts              Help
                                        > About Wireshark
                                        > Keyboard Shortcuts

expert system                           «M-a»
                                        > Expert information
# Alternatively, click on the colored disk icon in the bottom-left corner.

add comment for single packet           «C-M-c»
# Alternative:
                                        Edit
                                        > Packet Comments
                                        > Add New Comment…

add comment for whole capture           «C-M-S-c»
# Alternative:
                                        Statistics
                                        > Capture File Properties

open flow graph window                  Statistics
                                        > Flow Graph
# Also,  set  the "Limit  to  display  filter"  checkbox, to  remove  irrelevant
# packets.  And  select the desired flow  type in the "Flow  type" dropdown menu
# (e.g. "TCP flows"), to remove some overwhelming details about each packet.
